You don't have to use these Lightning LoRA combos. You can use other Lightning LoRAs instead.  
You can also disable the global Lightning LoRAs and assign, for example, **Combo 1 for Video 1**, **Combo 3 for Video 2**, and **Combo 2 for Video 3**.  
Each combo produces different motion and degradation behavior, which can help you fine-tune the final result.

The video quality will degrade even less if you don't use Lightning LoRAs, but it will take a very long time.

nodes.title: TUTO
widgets_values:
# Adding New Video Sections

You can add new sections very easily.  

1. Copy the **second section (10-second video)**, including:  
   - the **subgraph** and **Get-set nodes**  
   - the **LoRA High node**  
   - the **LoRA Low node**  
   
2. Paste it **next to section 2**.

3. Connect the **extented image output** to the **source image input 1** and **output** to the **prev_ samples input** of the new section.

> Tip: Make sure all node connections are intact to avoid missing input errors.

Don't skip sections, do them in order: 1, then 2, then 3. If you go from section 1 straight to section 3, there will be a cut.

> âš ï¸ **Important Quality Warning**  
> The longer the video is extended, the more the overall quality may gradually degrade over time.  
> This is expected behavior when chaining multiple video generations.

# Usage Tips (Longer Videos)

If you want to create videos longer than 5 seconds:

First, generate the first video.

If you donâ€™t like the result, simply change the seed and generate again.

If you like the video, enable the second video.  
The seed remains the same.  
The first video will not be generated again.  
Only the second video will be generated.

Repeat the same process for the following videos.

### Additional Tip
If the workflow appears empty or no nodes are visible (this can happen when opening subgraphs):  
Click **Fit View** in the Canvas menu.  
If the Canvas is not visible, enable it here:  
`Settings â†’ Canvas â†’ Lite Graph â†’ Show Graph Canvas`
To open a subgraph, click on the small icon in the top-left corner of the subgraph node.

nodes.title: loras 3 ksampler
widgets_values:
**High LoRA Explanation**

There are **two High LoRAs** available.

The **first High LoRA** corresponds to the **first KSampler without Lightning**.  
In most cases, it is **recommended to use it**, otherwise the Lightning LoRA may not be applied correctly.

If you are using a **custom or NSFW model**, it is recommended to **lower the LoRA weight**  
to keep **maximum image quality**.

nodes.title: triple ksampler steps cfg
widgets_values:
**Important**

Do **not** change the step values if you donâ€™t know how to use them.  
Wrong settings can make the video quality **very poor** or cause the generation to **stop**.

**Step Definitions**

- **Total Steps**  
  Total number of steps used for the whole generation.

- **No LoRA Steps**  
  Step where the **high-noise phase without LightX2V and without Lightning LoRA** ends.

- **High End Step**  
  Step where **high noise ends** and **low noise begins**, using **Lightning LoRA**.

You can also set **Total Steps = 6**.

**CFG**

CFG is set to **4**.  
This corresponds to the **first KSampler without Lightning** and helps create **more motion**.

If the animation looks **too fast or unstable**, you can lower it to **3**.
